However, if the purpose of the task is to check that the input matrix contains _all digits_, that is, there is no duplicate entry, then the separate `find` method should not be called.  Instead a boolean array is needed to check for duplicate entries:
```java
public boolean allDigitsPresent(int[][] arr) {
    boolean[] digitSet = new boolean[10];
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; arr.length; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j &lt; arr[i].length; j++) {
            int d = arr[i][j]; // digit
            if (d &lt;= 0 || d &gt;= digitSet.length) {
                return false; // invalid value in the matrix
            }
            if (digitSet[d]) { // already set, duplicate is found
                return false;
            }
            digitSet[d] = true;
        }
    }
    return true; // no duplicate digit is found, all digits are in range [1..9]
}
